{"word":"ἕλκος","slug":"ἕλκος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἕλκος</b></el> <el>(ἕλκος, εος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕλκω'><el>ἕλκω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a wound</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, attic<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a festering wound</i>, <el>ἕλκος ὕδρου</el> <i>the festering bite</i> of a serpent, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <i>of plague-ulcers</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a wound, loss</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}